Defendant Aaron Jones in court with attorney Jane Heather Christopherson.  Defendant Aaron Jones in custody.  Karl Peter Hayes appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
AS TO COUNT 2: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, with credit for 217 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  The court did not address if the defendant is/is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is/is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions:  
Serve 30 DAYS condition time in the House of Correction with huber for work; 
Court finds the defendant eligible for the interstate compact program.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank.
The Court is imposing the applicable fees, assessments, court costs, and surcharges, including a DNA assessment (and, you may have to give a swab, which you might be able to have expunged under 165.77) to be paid over the duration of probation failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
